Talat charges a full ball and smokes a drive back down the pitch to Nabi's left, he reaches up to stab at it left-handed and takes some steam off the ball as it bursts through and is fielded by long-off eventually. 10/10 on difficulty because of the pace it was coming back to him and he only got one hand to it. Commentary: looks stone dead and the finger goes up! Nabi with a clever change of line darting this flatter on off stump, it straightens and beats the attempted back foot flick by Talat trying to pinch a single to midwicket. Talat goes for the review. Seems more in hope than in belief that it will be overturned. Only way it's not out is if he was out outside the line of off stump, but the ball-tracker shows he was hit fully in line, not even umpire's call, and the ball was knocking back a fleshy part of the stumps. Aleem Dar's decision is upheld.
